        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 3:25PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 325 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bosque Bonita, moving northwest at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Indian Hot Springs, Indio Mountains Research Station, Bosque Bonita,
and Big Box.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
